<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code may call strcmp(StaticSym->Module, ModuleName) when ModuleName != NULL but StaticSym->Module == NULL. The function checks only StaticSym->Name for NULL; there is no guarantee StaticSym->Module is non-NULL, so strcmp can be invoked with a NULL pointer, causing out-of-bounds access/UB and thus violating MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>
